And, if you've all forgotten about the original film (the best one), there are Neanderthals living on Pangaea. That is far from the truth. text: The one good thing about this trailer for me is "Diesel Weasel" being back. If they really want to make one last chapter we could enjoy and take seriously, they should do a story about the humans returning to start occupying the land now that it's warmer.   It would be a territorial drama about the gang trying to find a new home while staying ahead of the tribe, which would be led by the now grown up human Manny, Sid, and Diego helped get back to his father as a baby in the original. When the chips are down though, they'd have to hope that the kid can remember the animals who saved his life. Manny would be in a position where he must choose between possibly killing the boy he once protected like his own child or risk losing his family as he did before.  Now THAT'S how you deliver an Ice Age finale! But no, instead, we get more of this pandering silliness. Sigh...

text: You know you guys, if your complaining about a new movie being made in a "movie series", you're kinds shooting your own foot when you go to the theaters to see it.  You do realize that the box office is one of the biggest contributors to whether a sequel is made or not(if one wasn't already planned beforehand)  Let me ask, which movie do you think is more likely to get a sequel, a movie with a good box office result or a movie with a bad box office result?  If you answered "The movie with the good box office result", then ask yourself "Am I tired of seeing new "Ice Age" sequels and do I want to contribute to this movie getting a good box office result, resulting in a higher chance of ANOTHER sequel being made?"  If you answered yes to both, then all you have to do is not go see it in theaters to contribute to lowering it's box office results thus lowering it's chance of getting a sequel.

They hardly had any scenes together and you would hardly know they were married with the lack of anything affectionate whatsoever. I'm not exaggerating, they had like two short scenes together. I'm sorry to say that I've lost faith with this franchise who are still talking about a sixth movie after being rated a 12 percent on their movie. They need to either come up with better storylines and focus on the interesting characters, or just let the series die already!
